    <div xml:id="PN353">
      <lg type="edition">
<l>ācil kammiyaṉ mācaṟap puṉainta</l>
<l>polañcey palkā caṇinta valku</l>
<l>līkaik kaṇṇi yilaṅkat taiit</l>
<l>tarumamo  ṭiyalvōḷ cāya ṉōkkit</l>
<l>tavirtta tērai viḷartta kaṇṇai</l>
<l>viṉava lāṉā velpō raṇṇal</l>
<l>yārmaka ḷeṉpōy kūṟak kēḷiṉik</l>
<l>kuṉṟukaṇ ṭaṉṉa nilaippal pōrpu</l>
<l>nāṭkaṭā vaḻitta naṉantalaik kuppai</l>
<l>valvi liḷaiyark kalkupata māṟṟāt</l>
<l>tolkuṭi maṉṉaṉ makaḷē muṉṉāṭ</l>
<l>kūṟi vanta māmutu vēntarkku</l>
<l>..................................</l>
<l>................yuḻakkik kuruti yōṭṭik</l>
<l>katuvāy pōkiya tutivā yeḵkamoṭu</l>
<l>pañciyuṅ kaḷaiyāp puṇṇa</l>
<l>rañcutaka vuṭaiyariva ṭaṉṉai mārē.</l>
</lg>
<lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>Looking at the grace of her who moves according to Dharma,</l>
<l>having attached, so that it shines, a golden chaplet,</l>
<l>[her] hips adorned with many beads made of gold,</l>
<l>crafted without flaw by a flawless artisan,</l>
<l>you who retains the chariot, you with eyes that have turned pale, </l>
<l>majesty victorious in war who does not stop asking [me],</l>
<l>who says “who is she?”, listen now to [what I have to] say:</l>
<l>She is the daughter of a king of an ancient family</l>
<l>who does not change the lasting readiness of [his] young warriors with strong bows,</l>
<l>with heaps of vast area destroyed daily by urging</l>
<l>into many heaps of a height as if one saw hills. On a former day,</l>
<l>to a great ancient king who came asking [for her],</l>
<l>………………………………..</l>
<l>…………………….ravaging, making the blood run,</l>
<l>with blades with pointed edges that have gone blunt,</l>
<l>with wounds from which the cotton has [not yet] been removed,</l>
<l>they are fit to evoke fear, her people.</l>
</lg>

    </div>
